== Rice ==

Pour @cold salted water{300%ml} into a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%mins}, then remove the pot from the heat.

Keep covered for another ~{10%mins} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

== Raita ==

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped) into small pieces.

Cut the @tomato{1}(diced) into 1cm chunks.

Place all the @diced tomato{1} and remaining onion, and @yoghurt{75%g} together in a #bowl{}.

Mix well then season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

== Chicken Jalfrezi ==

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks.

Roughly chop the @coriander{5%g}(stalks and all).

Place a separate #large pot{} over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Add the @diced Irish chicken breast{260%g}, chopped pepper and half the chopped onion.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Fry until chicken is browned all over, ~{5-6%mins}. Stir occasionally.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to vacuum packing we use to keep it fresh.

Reduce the heat to medium-high.

Pour in the @chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1%pack}, @harissa paste{1%sachet} and @chicken stock powder{1%sachet}.

Cover and simmer for ~{8-10%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When 2-3 mins of cooking time remain, stir in the @garam masala{1%sachet} and @sugar{1/2%tsp}.

Taste and season with salt, pepper and @sugar{to taste}.

== To Serve ==

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and divide between bowls.

Top with the chicken jalfrezi and serve the cooling raita alongside.

Garnish with a sprinkling of chopped coriander.